<span id="freeTextContainer11589384349322510267">Usually, I have one of three reactions to a book: I love it and plow through it, I hate it and put it down within 50 pages, or I like it and take my time, possibly reading other books simultaneously. This one ... oy. Because of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/119073.The_Name_of_the_Rose' title='The Name of the Rose by Umberto Eco' rel='nofollow noopener'> The Name of the Rose</a>, I kept expecting it to be good - or, more accurately, to get better. I waited 100 pages. Then 200 pages. Then 300 pages. Finally, I threw it across the room in frustration at 350 pages. I&apos;m still bitter.</span>
