<span id="freeTextContainer7791860967358157178">I really hated this book. I choked through it due to the sheer fortitude engendered by my unreasonable need to finish every book that I start. Every. Single. Book. Had I been able to dismiss it, I would have. A friend once told me that I should read Eco&apos;s essays, and that his fiction was an attempt to destroy overly-used literary devices of current literature by gluttonously indulging in them. I&apos;ve never actually bothered to look into whether or not it was true because, truthfully, it&apos;s the myth</span>
  <span id="freeText7791860967358157178" style="display:none">I really hated this book. I choked through it due to the sheer fortitude engendered by my unreasonable need to finish every book that I start. Every. Single. Book. Had I been able to dismiss it, I would have. A friend once told me that I should read Eco's essays, and that his fiction was an attempt to destroy overly-used literary devices of current literature by gluttonously indulging in them. I've never actually bothered to look into whether or not it was true because, truthfully, it's the myth I need to believe.</span>
