        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer13025440" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9698144700456863661">Bust out the champagne - I finished this book and my head didn&apos;t crack. It is one of the most amazing, yet difficult, books I&apos;ve ever read. The story presents itself on multiple levels: narrative, metaphoric, historical, imaginative, etc. I&apos;d give it five stars if it wasn&apos;t for the convoluted writing style, which made me want to give up numerous times. I forged ahead because the question of &quot;what&apos;s on the island?&quot; kept nagging me.<br/><br/>I loved the historical portrait of this period, when people were e</span>
  <span id="freeText9698144700456863661" style="display:none">Bust out the champagne - I finished this book and my head didn't crack. It is one of the most amazing, yet difficult, books I've ever read. The story presents itself on multiple levels: narrative, metaphoric, historical, imaginative, etc. I'd give it five stars if it wasn't for the convoluted writing style, which made me want to give up numerous times. I forged ahead because the question of "what's on the island?" kept nagging me.<br /><br />I loved the historical portrait of this period, when people were evolving towards a more rational world view while still tied to mythology and superstition. Some of their failed inventions and explanations sounded so logical. I had no idea that discovering how to calculate longitude was a matter of international espionage.<br /><br />If I read it again, I'd want to investigate all the historical references, which means I'd be glued to Wikipedia for the duration of the book. Most pages contain two or three references to things I don't understand, or languages I don't know. It was a daunting read but I'm glad I stuck with it.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9698144700456863661" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


