<span id="freeTextContainer12888199791542879132">Reading Umberto Eco is never an easy read but saying that, it doesn’t mean he’s not enjoyable. Added to the fact that all his books are translated from his native Italian, it is worth remembering. <br/>Sometimes two or three people are involved in the translation. He does write a good yarn, especially where historical fiction is concerned. <br/>I still think Focault’s Pendulum is his best work followed by The Prague Cemetery </span>

