              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7090198877895846924"><b><br/> A mixture of Don Quijote and Moby Dick, had come this novel. Intending to write a study about it soon. AS usual, the magician was playing, throwing his codes, here and there, waiting for his &quot;model reader&quot; to interpret, (and to EXTRA-interpret), and, as I was supposing while proceeding; it&apos;s a big metaphor, or, by his tongue: &quot; … they are mannered exercises&quot;.<br/><br/> Il maestro era un giocatore, un attore e un auonatore. <br/></b></span>
  <span id="freeText7090198877895846924" style="display:none"><b><br /> A mixture of Don Quijote and Moby Dick, had come this novel. Intending to write a study about it soon. AS usual, the magician was playing, throwing his codes, here and there, waiting for his "model reader" to interpret, (and to EXTRA-interpret), and, as I was supposing while proceeding; it's a big metaphor, or, by his tongue: " … they are mannered exercises".<br /><br /> Il maestro era un giocatore, un attore e un auonatore. <br /></b></span>
